comments: This term has been obsoleted to keep the structure simple.

definition.val: A portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) that is committed to the development of a root primordium (PO:0005029).

comments: Only detectable by gene expression, not morphology. May arise in a pericycle (PO:0006203), as for lateral roots in most seed plants, an endodermis (PO:0000252), as for lateral roots in ferns, or from parenchyma cells (PO:0000074) that are part a shoot axis (PO:0025029), in the case of a basal root (PO:0025002) or shoot-borne root (PO:0000042).

definition.val: A phyllome anlagen (PO:0025430) that will give rise to a cotyledon primordium (PO:0000015) and is part of a peripheral zone (PO:000225) of an embryo shoot apical meristem (PO:0006362).
A phyllome anlagen (PO:0025430) that will give rise to a vascular leaf primordium (PO:0000017) and is part of a peripheral zone (PO:0000225) of a shoot apical meristem (PO:0020148).

comments: This is the region where you have the maximum concentration of auxin in the SAM (at least in a few species that have been studied).

definition.val: A portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) that is part of a peripheral zone (PO:0000225) of a shoot apical meristem (PO:0020148) and will give rise to a phyllome primordium (PO:0025128).

comments: The phyllome anlagen is only detectable by gene expression, not morphology.

definition.val: A phyllome plate meristem (PO:0025428) in the vascular leaf (PO:0009025).

comments: The activity of a leaf plate meristem results in increase in the surface area, but not thickness of a vascular leaf (PO:0009025).

synonyms.val: meristema en placa de la hoja (Spanish, exact)
葉の板状分裂組織 (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: A portion of meristem (PO:0009013) tissue in which the planes of cell division in each layer are anticlinal to the surface of the phyllome (PO:0006001).

comments: The activity of a phyllome plate meristem results in increase in the surface area, but not thickness of a phyllome.

synonyms.val: フィロムplate分裂細胞 (Japanese, exact)
meristema en placa del filoma (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: A xylem development stage (PO:0025425) that has as primary participant a portion of secondary xylem (PO:0005848) tissue during the interval between the beginning of a cell division stage of secondary xylem (PO:0025463) and the death of the last living cell in the secondary xylem.

comments: During a secondary xylem development stage (also called a wood development stage), the cells of secondary xylem (PO:0005848), including tracheary elements (PO:0000290), xylem fiber cells (PO:0000274), and wood parenchyma cells (PO:0004525) undergo cellular developmental processes (GO:0048869) such as cell division (GO:0051301), cell growth (GO:0016049), cell differentiation (GO:0030154), or cell death (GO:0008219). The transition from sapwood to heartwood marks the end of the secondary xylem development stage.

synonyms.val: etapa de desarrollo del xilema secundario (Spanish, exact)
二次木質部発生過程 (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: A vascular tissue development stage (PO:0025424) that has as primary participant a portion of phloem (PO:0005417) tissue.

synonyms.val: etapa de desarrollo del floema (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: A vascular tissue development stage (PO:0025424) that has as primary participant a portion of xylem (PO:0005352) tissue.

synonyms.val: etapa de desarrollo del xilema (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: A plant tissue development stage (PO:0025423) that has as primary participant a portion of vascular tissue (PO:0009015).

synonyms.val: 維管束細胞発生過程 (Japanese, exact)
etapa de desarrollo del tejido vascular (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: A plant structure development stage (PO:0009012) that has as primary participant a portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007).

synonyms.val: 植物細胞発生過程 (Japanese, exact)
etapa de desarrollo de tejido vegetal (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: A xylem fiber cell (PO:0000274) in which the inner-most layer of the secondary cell wall (GO:0009531) contains abundant cellulose and is poor in lignin.

comments: Often found in reaction wood in dicots and in some phloem fiber cells (PO:0004519), as in Linum usitatissimum. In gelatinous fiber cells, the inner layer of the cell wall is a cellulosic gelatinous-layer or G-layer, which may be relatively porous and less compact than the outer layers of the cell wall and may absorb water and swell.

definition.val: A phloem fiber cell (PO:0004519) that has as parts one or more thin internal partitions or septa.

comments: A septatephloem fiber cell septum is composed of the adjacent primary cell walls of two internal cells that arise from mitosis within the septate phloem fiber cell after it has formed a secondary cell wall (GO:0009531).

synonyms.val: 隔壁師部 fiber cell (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: A gametophore axis that is a leafless extension of a gametophore stem or branch on which a sporophyte is borne.

comments: Raises the sporophyte above the perichaetial bracts. Found in Sphagnum and Andreaea.

definition.val: A portion of parenchyma tissue that forms a circular membrane extending from a spore capsule columella and attached to the ends of the peristome teeth that covers a spore capsule mouth.

comments: Present in some moss species of the family Polytrichaceae.

definition.val: A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) that is a single layer of cells on the outside of an antheridium (PO:0025125).

comments: Cells in the antheridium jacket layer surround the spermatogenous cells (PO:0025525) and do not give rise to antheridium sperm cells (PO:0025120).

synonyms.val: capa de la cubierta del anteridio (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: A native plant cell (PO:0025606) that is part of an antheridium jacket layer (PO:0030053).

synonyms.val: capa c&#233lular de la cubierta del anteridio (Spanish, exact)
造精器被覆層細胞 (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: A native plant cell (PO:0025606) at the base of a gemma (PO:0025614) or adjacent to a brachycyte (PO:0030058) that breaks down to allow abscission of the gemma or brachycyte.

comments: May be a single cell adjacent to a brachycyte (PO:0030058) or part of a portion of tmema tissue.

definition.val: A native plant cell (PO:0025606) that develops from a cell in a protonema (PO:0030003) and has a thick cell wall.

comments: Found in mosses. A brachycyte is a drought tolerant cell that can act as a gemma (PO:0025614) and may give rise to a new plant. Cells of a protonema (PO:0030003) may develop into brachycytes under stress. May form a chain or be separated by tmema cells (PO:0030059).

synonyms.val: 原糸体細胞の細胞壁を厚くした細胞、耐性細胞(brood cell?) (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: A native plant cell (PO:0025606) located at the base of a non-vascular leaf (PO:0025075) adjacent to where the leaf attaches to the stem (PO:0009047).

comments: Found in mosses. Alar cells occur in an area at the base of a leaf that may be triangular, ovate or rectangular and is sometimes called the alar region. They are different in size, shape, color, thickness, or ornamentation from other cells in the leaf.

definition.val: A native plant cell (PO:0025606) that divides to gives rise to a sporocyte (PO:0006204) and is part of a sporangium (PO:0025094).

comments: May also give rise to sterile cells such as elators (in liverworts) or tapetal cells. In most species outside seed plants, multiple archesporial cells are part of an archesporium or sporogenous tissue.

definition.val: An axillary hair terminal cell that is the long terminal cell of a gametophore axillary hair.

synonyms.val: 茎葉体腋毛終端細胞 (Japanese, exact)
c&#233lula terminal de pelo axilar del gamet&#243foro (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) that has as parts tmema cells (PO:0030059).

comments: Found in bryophytes at the base of a gemma (PO:0025614). Participates in abscission of the gemma.

definition.val: An axillary hair that grows in a leaf axil of a non-vascular leaf.

comments: Found in pleurocarpous mosses. Form in the axils of leaf primordia and may disappear when the gametophore is mature.

definition.val: A canal (PO:0025132) in the center of an archegonium neck (PO:0030039).

comments: During archegonium development, the archegonium neck canal cells (PO:0030065) and the ventral canal cell (PO:0025524) disintegrate, creating a archegonium neck canal for the plant sperm cells (PO:0000084) to enter the archegonium (PO:0025126).

synonyms.val: canal del cuello del arquegonio (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: A native plant cell (PO:0025606) that is one of the axial row of cells in an immature archegonium neck (PO:0030039).

comments: During archegonium development, the archegonium neck canal cells (PO:0030065) and the ventral canal cell (PO:0025524) disintegrate, creating a archegonium neck canal for the plant sperm cells (PO:0000084) to enter the archegonium (PO:0025126).

synonyms.val: c&#233lula del canal del cuello del arquegonio (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: An axillary hair basal cell that is part of a gametophore axillary hair base.

synonyms.val: 茎葉体腋毛基底細胞 (Japanese, exact)
c&#233lula basal del pelo axilar del gamet&#243foro (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: A axillary hair base that is the basal part of a gametophore axillary hair, below the gametophore axillary hair terminal cell.

comments: Consists of two to a dozen cells.

synonyms.val: base del pelo axilar del gamet&#243foro (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: A portion of epidermis (PO:0005679) tissue that is an outgrowth from the epidermis between the leaves of a gametophore axis (PO:0030020).

comments: Paraphyllia are much smaller than leaves and may be filamentous, scale-like, or leaf-like. Found in pleurocarpous mosses and a few leafy liverworts.

definition.val: An epidermal initial cell (PO:0000349) that gives rise to an epidermal rhizoid (PO:0030071).

comments: Part of the epidermis of a thallus or gametophore of a bryophyte or pteridophyte in the gametophytic phase or the stem of a monocot in the sporophytic phase.

synonyms.val: 表皮仮根始原細胞 (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: An protonema sub-apical initial that gives rise to a branch of a protonema.

comments: May give rise to a chloronema, caulonema, protonema rhizoid, tmema cell, or brachycyte.

synonyms.val: rama lateral inicial del protonema (Spanish, exact)
原糸体側枝始原細胞 (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: A portion of epidermis (PO:0005679) that is the outermost layer of a sporangium wall (PO:0025306).

comments: Develops from the outermost layer of an amphithecium in bryophytes.

definition.val: A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) that is a single or double strand in the center of a non-vascular leaf (PO:0025075) and has as part hydrome (PO:0030047) or leptome (PO:0030048).

comments: Found in bryophytes. Often contains both hydrome and leptome. Functions in support and conduction in a phyllid. The term costa is sometimes used for the midrib of monocot leaves, but this ontology class should only be used for non-vascular leaves.

definition.val: A rhizoid (PO:0030078) that develops from an epidermal rhizoid initial cell (PO:0030068).

comments: Found in bryophytes and pteridophytes growing from the epidermis of a gametophore or the lower surface of a thallus and in some monocots growing from the stem at the cotyledonary node. May be considered a type of trichome.

definition.val: A slender, usually uniseriate multicellular trichome (PO:0025162) that grows intermixed with the gametangia.

comments: Found in bryophytes and pteridophytes, especially in mosses.

definition.val: A protonema side branch initial that gives rise to a protonemal rhizoid.

synonyms.val: rama lateral inicial del rizoide proton&#233mico (Spanish, exact)
原糸体側枝仮根始原細胞 (Japanese, exact)

nodes.lbl: protonemal side branch rhizoid initial cell

definition.val: An umbrella-shaped cardinal organ part that is the apical portion of an archegoniophore and bears archegonia.

comments: Found in Marchantiales.

definition.val: A disk-shaped cardinal organ part (PO:0025001) that is the apical portion of an antheridiophore (PO:0030033) and bears antheridia (PO:0025125).

comments: Found in mosses and other bryophytes such as the liverwort Marchantiales.

definition.val: A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) that is the internal part of a sporangium (PO:0025094), bounded by the sporangium wall (PO:0025306), and has as parts archesporial cells (PO:0030056).

comments: Gives rise to sporocytes and may give rise to other sterile cells such as elators.

definition.val: A rhizoid that is part of a protonema and develops from a protonemal side branch rhizoid initial.
A plant structure (PO:0009011) that is a uniseriate filament with positive geotropism that grows from an epidermis (PO:0005679) or protonema (PO:0030003).

comments: May be unicellular or multicellular. Serves to anchor the plant to the substrate, and may function in nutrient and water uptake. Usually lacks chlorophyll. Includes epidermal rhizoids that grow from the epidermis of bryophytes and pteridophytes in the gametophytic phase or from the stems of some monocots, protonemal rhizoids that branch from a protonema, and rhizoids that develop from a basal cell of a gametophore bud.

definition.val: A gametophyte meristematic apical cell that is part of a rhizoid.

synonyms.val: c&#233lula apical meristem&#225tica del rizoide (Spanish, exact)
仮根分裂頂端細胞 (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) that is the outer layer or layers of a sporangium (PO:0025094) early in sporangium development (GO:0043582).

comments: Term used for bryophytes. May have one or more layers. An amphithecium may give rise to an exothecium and other layers of a sporangium wall (jacket layer or layers). In true mosses, the amphithecium gives rise to the sporangium wall and the peristome. In hornworts and peat mosses, it gives rise to the sporangium wall and sporogenous tissue.

synonyms.val: アンフィテシウム細胞 (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: A protonema sub-apical initial hat gives rise to a gametophore bud.

comments: In Physcomitrella patens, a gametophore bud initial typically is more bulbous than a protonema side branch initial, and its plane of first cell division is oblique, rather than perpendicular, to the plane of growth.

synonyms.val: 茎葉体芽始原細胞 (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: A protonema meristematic apical cell that is part of a chloronema.

synonyms.val: クロロネマ分裂頂端細胞 (Japanese, exact)
c&#233lula apical meristem&#225tica del cloronema (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: A protonema meristematic apical cell that is part of a caulonema.

synonyms.val: カウロネマ分裂頂端細胞 (Japanese, exact)
c&#233lula apical meristem&#225tica del caulonema (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: A lateral root (PO:0020121) that is sclerified and pointed.

comments: Lateral root spines cannot grow indeterminately or supply the plant with water and solutes. See JSTOR:43235457 for documentation of lateral root spines in Dioscorea prehensilis (Dioscoreaceae) and Moraea sp. (Iridaceae).

definition.val: An initial cell (PO:0004011) that is part of a gametophore (PO:0030018) and gives rise to a non-vascular leaf (PO:0025075).

comments: In Physcomitrella patens, non-vascular leaf initials arise from the daughter cells of a gametophore axis apical cell. Subsequent division of a non-vascular leaf initial establishes a non-vascular leaf apical cell.

synonyms.val: c&#233lula inicial de la hoja no vascular (Spanish, exact)
非維管束葉の始原細胞 (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: An initial cell that is produced by longitudinal division of a sub-apical cell of a protonema.

comments: May give rise to a branch of the protonema (including a protonema rhizoid, tmema cell or brachycyte), a gametophore bud, or may not divide further.

synonyms.val: c&#233lula subapical inicial del protonema (Spanish, exact)
原糸体次頂端始原細胞 (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: A portion of ground tissue (PO:0025059) that is the tissue internal to an amphithecium early in sporangium development.

comments: Term used for bryophytes. In liverworts an early sporangium endothecium produces sporogenous tissue. In Sphagnum, Andreaea, and hornworts, it produces columella and sporogenous tissue.

definition.val: A shoot-borne root (PO:0000042) that is sclerified and pointed.

comments: Shoot-borne root spines cannot grow indeterminately or supply the plant with water and solutes. See PO_REF:00015 for documentation of shoot-borne root spines in Acanthorhiza aculeata (Arecaceae).

definition.val: A fruit (PO:0009001) which develops from a gynoecium (PO:0009062) and at maturity comprises a dry exocarp (PO:0009085), dry mesocarp (PO:0009087), and dry endocarp (PO:0009086) that usually dehisce.

comments: Capsule fruits (PO:0030091) are divided into subcategories depending upon the location of sutures in the pericarp (PO:0009084) that the seeds (PO:0009010) are released through.

definition.val: A portion of root periderm (PO:0005047) formed in response to a disruption of the root epidermis (PO:0006036).

comments: Root periderm scars are lenticel-like structures on the tuberous roots (PO:0025523), primary roots (PO:0020127), and/or tuberous root tubers (PO:0025476) of plants such as sweet potato, cassava, parsnips, and carrots. Disruption of the epidermis by the emergence of a lateral root initiates a wound response which results in the production of a root periderm scar. Gas exchange does not occur through a root periderm scar.

definition.val: A capsule fruit (PO:0030091) which at maturity dehisces through pores on a pericarp (PO:0009084).

comments: Example: poppy (Papaver spp.).

definition.val: A capsule fruit (PO:0030091) which at maturity dehisces through both the fruit septa (PO:0025268) and the fruit locules (PO:0025270).

comments: When annotating to a capsule fruit (PO:0030091) which only dehisces through the fruit septa (PO:0025268), annotate to septicidal capsule fruit (PO:0030093). When annotating to a capsule fruit which only dehisces through the fruit locules (PO:0025270), annotate to loculicidal capsule fruit (PO:0030092). Examples: physic nut (Jatropha curcas) and Manihot brachyloba.

definition.val: A capsule fruit (PO:0030091) which dehisces through a fruit septa (PO:0025268).

comments: When annotating to a capsule fruit (PO:0030091) which dehisces through both the fruit septa (PO:0025268) and fruit locules (PO:0025270), annotate to coccarium capsule fruit (PO:0030094). When annotating to a capsule fruit which only dehisces through the fruit locules, annotate to loculicidal capsule fruit (PO:0030092). Examples: dutchman's pipe (Aristolochia elegans) and black cottonwood (Populus trichocarpa).

definition.val: A capsule fruit (PO:0030091) which at maturity dehisces through fruit locules (PO:0025270).

comments: When annotating to a capsule fruit (PO:0030091) which dehisces through both the fruit septa (PO:0025268) and fruit locules (PO:0025270), annotate to coccarium capsule fruit (PO:0030094). When annotating to a capsule fruit which only dehisces through the fruit septa, annotate to septicidal capsule fruit (PO:0030093). Examples: cotton (Gossypium raimondii) and rose mallow (Hibiscus syriacus).

definition.val: A shoot meristematic apical cell that is part of a gametophore.

comments: Occurs in the non-vascular shoot system of the gametophyte of mosses and leafy liverworts.

synonyms.val: 茎葉体分裂組織の頂端細胞 (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: A shoot system (PO:0009006) that consists of the shoot axes (PO:0025029) and non-vascular leaves (PO:0025075) of a plant in the gametophyte development stage (PO:0028003) .

comments: A gametophore is the leafy part of the gametophyte of mosses and leafy liverworts, excluding the protonema. Develop from buds that form on the protonema. Antheridia and archegonia arise on the gametophore.

synonyms.val: 茎葉体, 蘚苔類の配偶体 (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: A plant anatomical space that is the opening on the apical end of a spore capsule.

comments: May be covered by a peristome.

synonyms.val: boca de la c&#225psula productora de esporas (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) that is the region of the endosperm closest to the micropyle of the seed.
A shoot axis meristematic apical cell at the tip of a seta.

comments: Ceases being an apical cell when the sporangium begins to develop.

synonyms.val: 柄分裂組織の頂端細胞 (Japanese, exact)
c&#233lula apical de la seta (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) that is the part of the endosperm (PO:0009089) nearest the chalazal region of the plant ovule (PO:0020003) and forming a cyst-like structure.

comments: Not in current literature. More like an attribute.

definition.val: A shoot meristematic apical cell that is part of a leaf apex.

comments: Occurs in the non-vascular leaves of bryophytes and the vascular leaves of some ferns. Only in plants where leaf growth is apical.

synonyms.val: c&#233lula apical de la hoja (Spanish, exact)
葉分裂組織の頂端細胞 (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: A shoot meristematic apical cell that is part of a shoot apex.

comments: Divides to produces leaf initial cells (if leaves are present) and other stem or branch tissues.

synonyms.val: c&#233lula apical del eje del epiblasto (Spanish, exact)
シュート軸分裂組織の頂端細胞 (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: A portion of shoot system epidermis (PO:0006035) that is part of a nectary (PO:0009035) .
A meristematic apical cell that is part of a whole plant in the sporophytic phase.

comments: Occurs in pteridophytes and the sporophyte of bryophytes.

synonyms.val: 胞子体分裂組織の頂端細胞 (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: An apical cell that is part of a whole plant in the gametophytic phase.

comments: Occurs bryophytes and pteridophytes.

synonyms.val: 配偶体分裂組織の頂端細胞 (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: A leaf meristematic apical cell (PO:0030011) that is part of a leaf apex of a non-vascular leaf.

comments: Occurs in the non-vascular leaves of bryophytes, which grow by division of a single, wedge-shaped apical cell with two cutting faces.

synonyms.val: 維管束を持たない葉の分裂組織の頂端細胞 (Japanese, exact)
c&#233lula apical de la hoja no vascular (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: A leaf meristematic apical cell that is part of the leaf apex of a vascular leaf.

comments: Occurs in vascular leaves of some ferns in their sporophytic phase.

synonyms.val: c&#233lula apical de la hoja vascular (Spanish, exact)
維管束を持つ葉の分裂組織の頂端細胞 (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: A portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) that is the outermost layer of a shoot apical meristem (PO:0020148) and gives rise to a shoot system epidermis (PO:0006035).

comments: The cells of the meristem L1 layer divide in a strictly anticlinical fashion.

definition.val: A portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) directly beneath a meristem L1 layer (PO:0009020) in a shoot apical meristem (PO:0020148) which gives rise to ground tissue (PO:0025059).

comments: Cells in the first subepidermal layer, the L2, divide in a largely anticlinal fashion, forming a completely separate population of cells from the other cell layers. Within developing organs, the meristem L2 layer divides anticlinally and periclinally.

definition.val: A portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) beneath a meristem L2 layer (PO:0009021) in a shoot apical meristem (PO:0020148) which gives rise to internal tissues of leaf and stem.

comments: The meristem L3 layer cells frequently divide in various orientations.

definition.val: A structure upon which (or in the axil of which) one or more megasporangia are borne; in flowering plants, a carpel.
A structure on which one or more microsporangia are borne; in flowering plants, the stamen.
A microsporophyll bearing one or more microsporangia.

comments: Part of tassel floret.

definition.val: An axil that is the space between a shoot axis and a leaf that branches from the shoot axis.
A leaf (PO:0025034) in a vascular plant.

comments: Has vascular tissue. From APweb Glossary: In angiosperms, commonly thought of as one of the three basic parts of the seed plant body, a structure usually of determinate growth, without secondary thickening, and of superficial origin, often flattened and photosynthetic in part, and in the axil of which is found a bud. Occurs in the sporophytic phase of a plant life cycle.

synonyms.val: 維管束のある葉, または維管束植物の葉 (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: A leaf-like organ on which one or more sporangia are borne.
A plant organ that is the base of a whole plant in the sporophytic phase and attaches it to the gametophore.

comments: Found in bryophytes and some pteridophytes. In mosses, the foot is located below the seta. In ferns, the foot is formed from the upper hypobasal quandrant of the embryo. The sporophyte foot serves for both attachment and absorption. The outer portion of the foot is composed of absorptive transfer cells.

definition.val: A bract (PO:0009055) that subtends an antheridium (PO:0025125).

comments: When an antheridium occurs on a specialized lateral branch of the gametophore, all of the phyllomes on that branch are usually perigonial bracts. If an antheridium occurs on a main axis of the gametophore, usually only the terminal phyllomes are perigonial bracts.

definition.val: A whole plant in the gametophytic phase that has a flat growth form and no distinct organs.

comments: A thallus is a gametophyte of liverworts and pteridophytes and develops from a short-lived protonema. Roughly two dimensional growth results from division of a single apical cell. Thalli may be ribbon or heart shaped or almost filamentous. Although there are no distinct organs, there may be tissue differentiation and dichotomous branching.

definition.val: A whole plant (PO:0000003) that participates in the plant embryo stage (PO:0007631).

comments: A plant embryo is generally formed after the first division of a plant zygote (PO:0000423), but in the case of a nucellar (adventitious) plant embryo (PO:0004537), somatic plant embryo (PO:0025302), microspore-derived cultured plant embryo (PO:0025305), and other embryos that arise through apogamy, it begins after the division of a single cell that is not a zygote. The end of the embryo stage varies among taxa; the beginning of a seed germination stage (PO:0007057) in seed plants, formation of the first vascular leaf (PO:0009025) in pteridophytes, the beginning of development of a sporangium (PO:0025094) in bryophytes, or the beginning of the formation of a plant organ (PO:0009008) such as a root (PO:0009005), shoot axis (PO:0025029), or vascular leaf (PO:0009025) in a cultured plant embryo (PO:0000010).

definition.val: A stem that is part of a gametophore.

comments: A stem (the primary axis) of the leafy part of a bryophyte shoot system.

definition.val: A branch that is part of a gametophore.

comments: A branch of the leafy part of a bryophyte shoot system.

definition.val: A shoot axis (PO:0025029) that is part of a gametophore (PO:0030018).

comments: Found in mosses and leafy liverworts. A stem or branch of the leafy part of a bryophyte.

definition.val: A vegetative bud that develops into a gametophore.

comments: Occurs in mosses and leafy liverworts. Develops from a caulonema cell in mosses.

definition.val: A gametophyte apical cell that is part of a thallus.

synonyms.val: 葉状体分裂組織の頂端細胞 (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: A shoot axis meristematic apical cell at the tip of a shoot apex in a shoot system that has as part vascular tissue.

comments: Occurs in some ferns in their sporophytic phase.

synonyms.val: c&#233lula apical del eje del epiblasto vascualr (Spanish, exact)
維管束を持つシュート軸分裂組織の頂端細胞 (Japanese, exact)

nodes.lbl: vascular shoot axis meristematic apical cell

definition.val: A shoot axis meristematic apical cell at the tip of a gametophore axis.

comments: Occurs at the tips of the stems and branches of bryophytes.

synonyms.val: 茎葉体軸分裂組織の頂端細胞 (Japanese, exact)
c&#233lula apical del eje del gamet&#243foro (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: A multi-tissue plant structure (PO:0025496) that develops from a plant ovule (PO:0020003) and has as parts a plant embryo (PO:0009009) enclosed in a seed coat (PO:0009088).

comments: A seed generally develops from an ovule (PO:0020003) after fertilization, but may develop without fertilization in the case of apogamy (e.g., adventitious embryos or somatic embryos). A seed is a reproductive unit of seed plants (gymnosperms, angiosperms, and fossil pteridosperms).

definition.val: A plant anatomical entity (PO:0025131) that is, or was, part of a plant, or was derived from a part of a plant.

comments: 'Part' includes both proper parts and the whole plant. CARO:0000003 'connected anatomical structure' is defined as: Material anatomical entity that is a single connected structure with inherent 3D shape, generated by coordinated expression of the organism's own genome.

definition.val: OBSOLETE. Tissues other than the vascular tissues, epidermis and the periderm.

comments: Replaced by portion of ground tissue (). Uninformative definition. Check it again.

definition.val: A pulvinus (PO:0009000) of an inflorescence branch (PO:0009081).

synonyms.val: pulv&#237nulo ramificado de una inflorescencia (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: A transfer cell that is part of a basal endosperm transfer layer.

comments: Responsible for transferring nutrients to an embryo by symplastic or apoplastic methods.

synonyms.val: c&#233lula de transferencia del endosperma basal (Spanish, exact)
基底胚乳転送細胞 (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: OBSOLETE. A cell layer found in basal endosperm transfer cell.

comments: This term was made obsolete because the definition was wrong. Replace by new term with same name but corrected definition.

synonyms.val: capa de transferencia del endosperma basal obsoleto (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: A stage in the life of a plant structure (PO:0009011) during which the plant structure undergoes developmental processes.

comments: Refers to GO:0032502 'developmental process', which includes growth, differentiation, and senescence, and BFO:0000003 'ocurrent'.

synonyms.val: etapa de desarrollo de estructura vegetal (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) in which plant cells (PO:0009002) have retained their embryonic characteristics, or have reverted to them secondarily, and that divide to produce new cells that can undergo differentiation to form mature tissues, i.e. they have a capacity for morphogenesis and growth.
OBSOLETE. A portion of plant tissue that covers the surface of the plant.

comments: This term is redundant with epidermis and will be obsoleted. Move annotations to epidermis.

definition.val: A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) that has as part one or more tracheary elements (PO:0000290) or sieve elements (PO:0025406).

comments: Functions in conduction and support. In shoot axes (PO:0025029), vascular tissue is often found as part of a shoot axis stele (PO:0025198) or as scattered vascular bundles (PO:0005020). May include other types of tissues or cells, such as parenchyma (PO:0005421) or fiber cells (PO:0025407).

synonyms.val: 維管束細胞の一部 (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: A cardinal organ part (PO:0025001) that is the elongated, apical part of an archegonium (PO:0025126).

comments: Early in development, the archegonium neck is occluded by a single row of neck canal cells (PO:0030065). At maturity, the neck canal cells (PO:0030065) and the ventral canal cell (PO:0025524) disintegrate, creating a archegonium neck canal (PO:0030066) for the plant sperm cells (PO:0000084) to enter the archegonium (PO:0025126).

definition.val: A cardinal organ part (PO:0025001) that is the enlarged basal part of an archegonium (PO:0025126) and has an archegonium egg cell (PO:0025122) located in it.

comments: After fertilization, the venter develops into the spore capsule calyptra (PO:0030037), which protects the sporangium (syn: spore capsule; PO:0025094) containing the developing sporophyte.

definition.val: A stalk (PO:0025066) that supports an antheridium head (PO:0030075).

comments: Found in mosses and other bryophytes such as the liverwort Marchantiales.

definition.val: A stalk (PO:0025066) that supports a spore capsule, the sporangium (PO:0025094).

comments: Found in some bryophytes, especially mosses and liverworts.

synonyms.val: とげ、剛毛、コケの柄 (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: A collective phyllome structure that consists of two or more of the most distal perichaetal bracts on a gametophore axis and surround a capsule.

comments: The perichaetal bracts may fuse laterally in the gametophytic perianth. The gametophytic perianth is not the same structure as a perianth (PO:0009058) in angiosperms.

definition.val: A bract (PO:0009055) that subtends an archegonium (PO:0025126).

comments: When an archegonium occurs on a specialized lateral branch of the gametophore, all of the phyllomes on that branch are usually perichaetal bracts. If an archegonium occurs on a main axis of the gametophore, only the terminal phyllomes are usually perichaetal bracts. The two or three terminal-most perichaetal bracts may fuse to form a gametophytic perianth.

definition.val: A cardinal organ part (PO:0025001) that develops from an archegonium (PO:0025126) and is a cap or hood enclosing the sporangium (syn: spore capsule; PO:0025094).

comments: Found in bryophytes. The spore capsule calyptra is a membranous or hairy cap or hood, composed of gametophytic tissue (venter; PO:0030038) that protects the embryonic sporophyte within the archegonium (PO:0025126). In some species, it may persist after the sporophyte develops and gets carried upward as the seta (PO:0030032) elongates. The spore capsule calyptra is usually lost before the spores are released, and its shape can be used for identification purposes.

synonyms.val: caliptra de la c&#225psula productora de esporas (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: A stalk (PO:0025066) that the basal part of an archegonium (PO:0025126).

comments: Raises the venter above the rest of the gametophyte.

definition.val: A stalk (PO:0025066) that is the basal part of an antheridium (PO:0025125).

comments: The antheridium stalk raises the antheridium (PO:0025125) from the antheridium head (PO:0030075).

definition.val: A stalk (PO:0025066) that supports an archegonium head (PO:0030034).

comments: Found in Marchantiales.

definition.val: A cardinal organ part (PO:0025001) at the apex or base of a petiole, petiolule, leaf sheath, or branch that is differentiated from the remaining organ parts by its enlarged cross section.

comments: Often glandular. Often involved in movement of a plant structure in response to touch, gravity or light. In panicoid grasses a swollen region in the stem above the intercalary meristem. Such a definition would also include stems of Chloranthaceae, Acanthaceae, Caryophyllaceae, Amaranthaceae, etc. [source: APweb:Glossary].

definition.val: A cardinal organ part that is the basal (distal) part of a sporangium.

comments: Term used for bryophytes and pteridophytes. The sporangium base is the sterile part of the sporangium below the sporangium theca. If swollen and distinct from the rest of the sporangium, it is called an apophysis or hypophysis.

definition.val: A plant axis (PO:0025004) that lacks shoot axis nodes (PO:0005004) and usually grows indeterminately.

comments: Roots function in the absorption of water and inorganic nutrients, anchoring the plant body to the substrate and supporting it, storage of food and nutrients, and vegetative reproduction. The roots of most vascular plant species enter into symbiosis with soil-borne microorganisms. Roots are usually positively geotropic and found underground, although there are many exceptions such as the aerial roots of orchids. Roots often form secondary thickening from the root lateral meristem (PO:0006308). Commonly thought of as one of the three basic parts of the plant body, along with the shoot axis (PO:0025029) and leaves (PO:0025034).

definition.val: A collective plant organ structure (PO:0025007) that produces shoot-borne portions of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) and the plant structures (PO:0009011) that arise from them.

comments: The shoot system is generally used to refer to the above-ground plant parts, although some plants have parts of their shoot system underground. For example, a rhizome (PO:0004542), bulb (PO:0025356), a corm (PO:0025355) or a subterranean tuber (PO:0004547), as in Solanum tuberosum (potato) or yam, are all part of the shoot system.

synonyms.val: シュート系、苗条系 (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: A plant structure (PO:0009011) that consists predominantly of similarly specialized plant cells (PO:0009002) of one or more types.

comments: A portion of plant tissue may contain one or several types of cells that are organized in a specific spatial arrangement into a structural unit (which includes a mass of callus) and may include an intercellular matrix. May include other types of isolated cells, such as idioblasts.

synonyms.val: porci&#243n de un tejido vegetal (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: A multi-tissue plant structure (PO:0025496) that is a functional unit, is a proper part of a whole plant (PO:0000003), and includes portions of plant tissue (PO:0009007) of at least two different types that derive from a common developmental path.

comments: Examples include stem (PO:0009047), leaf (PO:0025034), and root (PO:0009005). May include individual plant cells (PO:0009002) that are not part of a portion of plant tissue (e.g., idioblasts, PO:0000283). A plant organ may have one or more different plant organs as parts, such as a sporophyll (PO:0009026) that may have as part a sporangium (PO:0025094) or a carpel (PO:0009030) that may have as part a plant ovule (PO:0020003).

definition.val: A multi-tissue plant structure (PO:0025496) that develops from a gynoecium (PO:0009062), or a single carpel (PO:0009030), and at maturity may have as parts one or more seeds (PO:0009010).

comments: A fruit (PO:0009001) may contain additional plant structures (PO:0009011) that were part of a flower (PO:0009046) and mature along with the gynoecium, such as a receptacle (PO:0009064). A fruit may develop without fertilization in cases of parthenocarpy, apomixis, or other hormone-induced conditions and may not always contain seeds (PO:0009010). When annotating to fruit (PO:0009001) that are referred to as ‘aggregate’, ‘multiple’, or ‘compound’, please annotate directly to the appropriate plant structure, such as receptacle, hypanthium (PO:0009065) or infructescence (PO:0006342). Fruits only occur in angiosperms.

definition.val: A cell which is a plant structure (PO:0009011).

comments: Applies to cells that are living or dead at maturity (e.g., fiber cell or tracheid) and includes any external encapsulating structures (if present) such as the plasma membrane and the plant-type cell wall. Definition of cell GO:0005623: "The basic structural and functional unit of all organisms. Includes the plasma membrane and any external encapsulating structures such as the cell wall and cell envelope". GO:0009505. Definition of plant-type cell wall (GO:0009505): A more or less rigid structure lying outside the cell membrane of a cell and composed of cellulose and pectin and other organic and inorganic substances, synonym; exact: cellulose and pectin-containing cell wall.

definition.val: OBSOLETE. A plant structure that is a product of fertilization and produces spores through meiosis.

comments: Replace_by whole plant (PO: PO:0000003) in the sporophyte development phase (PO:0028003). Structures that only occur in sporophyte should have participates_in relation to sporophytic development phase.

definition.val: OBSOLETE. A plant structure that arises through meiosis and may produce gametes by mitosis.

comments: Replace_by whole plant in the gametophyte phase (PO:0028002). The gametophyte arises from the product of meiosis (the spore). Structures that occur only in gametophytes should have a participates_in relation to the gametophyte phase.

definition.val: A portion of ground tissue (PO:0025059) that is the sub-epidermal layer of a sporangium wall (PO:0025306).

comments: Term used for vascular plants to describe the outermost layer of a sporangium wall that is internal to the exothecium.

synonyms.val: endotecio de la pared del esporangio (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: A cardinal organ part that is the apical part of a spore capsule that separates from the rest of the capsule during dehiscence.

comments: Found in mosses. May remain partly attached to the rest of the capsule.

synonyms.val: op&#233rculo de la c&#225psula productora de esporas (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: A cardinal organ part that is a single lobe of a peristome.

comments: Generally triangular. Peristome teeth may be simple or compound, and may be attached by their tips to the epiphragm.

synonyms.val: 蒴歯歯片、縁歯歯片,　歯環を構成する個々の歯(Japanese, exact)

definition.val: A single or double circle of peristome teeth inside a sporangium mouth.

comments: The peristome is located under the operculum, if an operculum is present. Upon maturity of a capsule, the teeth of the peristome open to release the spores.

definition.val: A cardinal organ part that is the main body of a sporangium and has spores located in it.

comments: Term used for bryophytes and pteridophytes.

definition.val: A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) that has as parts leptoid (PO:0025033) cells and cells of no other types.

comments: A leptome is composed of only leptoids (PO:0025033). Found in bryophytes, in non-vascular shoot axes such as a gametophore axis or seta (PO:0030032) or in the midrib of a non-vascular leaf. Often surrounding a central hydrome. May function in the conduction of organic substances, similar to phloem in vascular plants.

definition.val: A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) that has as parts hydroid (PO:0025032) cells and cells of no other types.

comments: A hydrome is composed of only hydroids. Found in bryophytes, in the center of a non-vascular shoot axis (PO:0025029) such as a gametophore (PO:0030018) or seta (PO:0030032). Often surrounded by the leptome (PO:0030048). May function in water conduction and may provide support.

definition.val: A gametophyte meristematic apical cell that is part of a protonema.

synonyms.val: 原糸体、糸状体の分裂組織の頂端細胞 (Japanese, exact)
c&#233lula meristem&#225tica apical del protonema (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: A ground tissue cell with thickened cell walls.

comments: Found only in bryophytes in gametophore axes, setae, or leaves. Functions in support rather than conduction. May or may not retain a living protoplast at maturity.

definition.val: A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) that is an axial strand in the center of a gametophore axis (PO:0030020) or seta (PO:0030032) and has as part a hydrome (PO:0030047) or a leptome (PO:0030048).

comments: Often contains both hydrome and leptome. Found in bryophytes. The term central strand is sometimes used to describe a protostele in vascular plants, but this ontology class should only be used for non-vascular plants. Analogous to a vein or vascular bundle in vascular plants.

definition.val: A portion of ground tissue (PO:0025059)  that has as parts stereid cells (PO:0030045) and no other cell types.

comments: A stereome is composed of only stereids. Found only in bryophytes in gametophore axes or non-vascular leaves. May function in support.

definition.val: A phyllome vascular system (PO:0025206) that includes the totality of the portions of vascular tissue in their specific arrangement in a carpel (PO:0009030).
A phyllome vascular system (PO:0025206) that includes the totality of the portions of vascular tissue in their specific arrangement in a stamen (PO:0009029).
An ear spikelet (PO:0006320) which is the ultimate, sessile, higher order inflorescence axis (PO:0009081) of the maize ear inflorescence (PO:0020136).

comments: Develops from the ear spikelet pair meristem (PO:0006360).

synonyms.val: espiga s&#233sil de la espiguilla (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: An ear spikelet (PO:0006320) which is the ultimate, pedicellate, higher order inflorescence axis (PO:0009081) of the maize ear inflorescence (PO:0020136).

comments: Develops from the ear spikelet pair meristem (PO:0006360).

synonyms.val: espiga pedicelada de la espiguilla (Spanish, exact)
雌穂（花）の有柄小穂 (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: A shoot system vascular system (PO:0025205) that includes the totality of the portions of vascular tissue in their specific arrangement in a flower (PO:0009046).

comments: Because a vascular system is defined as the totality of the portions of vascular tissue in a plant structure, the vascular systems of floral parts are part of the flower vascular system.

synonyms.val: sistema vascular de la flor (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: OBSOLETE. A false septum formed by the ingrowth from the placenta of an ovary rather than from the carpel walls. This is formed post fertilization.

comments: This term was made obsolete to avoid confusion with the new terms fruit replum and ovary replum. Consider ovary replum (PO:0025272) or fruit replum (PO:0025267).

definition.val: An intercalary meristem (PO:0006073) that is part of a stem internode (PO:0020142) and is intercalated between two portions of non-meristematic tissue.

comments: Results in an increase in length of a stem internode, as part of primary growth.

definition.val: An ear floret that is the lower of the two florets of a pedicellate spikelet rachilla of an ear inflorescence.

comments: The lower floret on the ear does not usually develop into a functional one.

synonyms.val: 雌穂（花）の有柄小穂の下位小花 (Japanese, exact)
florete inferior de la espiguilla s&#233sil de la espiga (Spanish, exact)

nodes.lbl: lower floret of pedicellate spikelet of ear

definition.val: A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) that is composed of plant ovary outer epidermis (PO:0005023), plant ovary inner epidermis (PO:0005024), and a plant ovary wall middle layer (PO:0005025)
An ear floret that is one of the two florets placed above the lower floret on a sessile spikelet rachilla of an ear inflorescence.

comments: This floret usually develops into a functional one.

synonyms.val: florete superior de la espiguilla s&#233sil de la espiga (Spanish, exact)
雌穂（花）の無柄小穂の上位小花 (Japanese, exact)

nodes.lbl: upper floret of sessile spikelet of ear

definition.val: A phyllome margin (PO:0025018) which is part of a sepal (PO:0009031).
A portion of vascular tissue (PO:0009015) that is a unit strand of the vascular system (PO:0000034) and has as part xylem (PO:0005352) or phloem (PO:0005417).

comments: May also contain portions of ground tissue (PO:0025059). The bundle sheath (PO:0006023) can also be part of a vascular bundle, if it is present.

definition.val: An ear floret that is the lower of the two florets on a sessile spikelet of an ear inflorescence.

comments: This floret does not usually develop into a functional one.

synonyms.val: florete inferior de la espiguilla pedicelada de la espiga (Spanish, exact)
雌穂（花）の無柄小穂の下位小花 (Japanese, exact)

nodes.lbl: lower floret of sessile spikelet of ear

definition.val: An ear floret that is the upper of the two florets of a pedicellate spikelet rachilla of an ear inflorescence.

comments: The upper floret on the ear usually develops into a functional one.

synonyms.val: 雌穂（花）の有柄小穂の上位小花 (Japanese, exact)
florete superior de la espiguilla pedicelada de la espiga (Spanish, exact)

nodes.lbl: upper floret of pedicellate spikelet of ear

definition.val: Multinucleate cell developed by a series of events involving kayokinesis but not cytokinesis of the initial feeding cell. The events are induced by root knot nematodes (e.g., Meloidogyne sp. ) entering the feeding cells (any cells) of the root vascular system.

synonyms.val: c&#233lula gigante de la ra&#237z (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: A portion of chlorenchyma tissue (PO:0005426) that is part of the plant ovary wall (PO:0005022) and is composed of mesophyll cells (PO:0004006).

comments: In some species, such as Arabidopsis, there may be a distinct subepidermal adaxial cell layer. The cells in the mesophyll layer(s) may not differentiate similar to the spongy and palisade cells found in the leaf mesophyll.

synonyms.val: capa media de la pared del ovario (Spanish, exact)
middle layer of plant ovary wall (exact)

definition.val: A portion of ovary epidermis (PO:0006063) which is the inner surface of a plant ovary (PO:0009072).

synonyms.val: 子房の表側、向軸側の表皮 (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: A portion of ovary epidermis (PO:0006063) which is the outer surface of a plant ovary (PO:0009072).

synonyms.val: 子房の裏側 背軸側の表皮 (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: A small, pistillate flower (PO:0025599) that is part of a ear spikelet (PO:0006320).

comments: The ear floret (PO:0006354) initiates both carpels (PO:0009030) and stamens (PO:0009029), but all stamens abort during development. Found in Zea spp.

definition.val: A vascular leaf that is distinct from adult leaves, being characterized by particular anatomical traits namely, wax and trichome distribution, presence or absence of epidermal cell types, cell wall shape and biochemistry.

comments: Many species have juvenile leaves at the base of the stem, adult leaves at the apex, and transition leaves in between. In maize, juvenile leaves are at the tip of the stalk (stem), which differentiates first, with adult leaves at the base, while other grasses may have other arrangements. The first juvenile leaves in Poaceae are the embryonic leaves found in the grass kernel (caryopsis).

definition.val: OBSOLETE. A thin partition or membrane that divides a cavity or a mass of tissue in the fruit that is derived from the carpel septum.

comments: This term was made obsolete because it was ambiguous. It has been replaced by the more precise terms fruit septum (PO:0025268) and fruit replum (PO:0025267). Annotations for Arabidopsis should go to fruit replum.

definition.val: OBSOLETE. A structure consisting of long multinucleate tubes in which latex is found, having no cross walls.

comments: This term was made obsolete because a nom-articulated laticifer is not a tissue type but consists of a single cell. Use non-articulated laticifer cell (PO:0006222) instead.

definition.val: A vascular leaf that is part of a plant embryo and is one of the first few leaves to develop from the embryonic shoot apical meristem.

comments: This term is used to described not yet fully-developed leaves that are part of an embryo.

definition.val: A plant structure (PO:0009011) that is part of an plant embryo (PO:0009009).

comments: Includes plant structures that only occur in embryos (such as suspensor) as well as plant structures that are part of an embryo when a plant is in the embryonic phase (such as embryonic radicle).

definition.val: A portion of secretory tissue (PO:0005656) that has as parts articulated laticifer cells (PO:0006221).

comments: The articulated laticifer cells are joined longitudinally to form a tube, with cross-walls that may be partially to fully perforated.

synonyms.val: 連合乳管（有節乳管） (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: A cardinal organ part (PO:0025001) of a shoot axis (PO:0025029) that is between two shoot axis nodes (PO:0005004).
An outgrowth of the seed funicle, that forms a bridge between the seed micropyle and other tissues. It is also a remnant form of the obturator found in the ovular funicle.
A phyllome trichome that is part of a bract epidermis.
A portion of phyllome epidermis (PO:0025157) that is part of a stamen (PO:0009029).
A portion of phyllome epidermis (PO:0025157) that is part of a carpel (PO:0009030).

synonyms.val: A portion of carpel epidermis (PO:0025096) that covers the abaxial surface of a carpel (PO:0009030). (broad)

definition.val: A portion of parenchyma tissue (PO:0005421) that is part of a root (PO:0009005).
A plant organ (PO:0009008) in which plant spores (PO:0025017) are produced.

comments: In bryophytes, particularly in mosses, a sporangium is referred to as a capsule. In seed plants, a sporangium is located in a sporophyll. In pteridophytes, a sporangium is located on the surface of a sporophyll or fertile leaf or borne on a sporangiophore. May be unicellular in some algae.

definition.val: OBSOLETE. A thin partition or membrane that divides multilocular ovary. Often found in species with syncarpous (multiple carpels fused) pistil.

comments: Carpel septum was made obsolete because it was ambiguous. It has been replaced by the more precise terms ovary septum (PO:0025262) and ovary replum (PO:0025272). Annotations for Arabidopsis should go to ovary replum (PO:0025272).

definition.val: A dehiscence zone (PO:0025092) that is part of a spore capsule.

comments: Found in bryophytes. The capsule annulus is located at the base of an operculum. Upon capsule maturation, cell separation in the annulus allows the operculum to separate from the capsule, aiding in spore dispersal.

synonyms.val: anillo de la c&#225psula de musgos (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) that is part of a plant structure and consists of a narrow band of cells that undergoes dehiscence upon maturation of the structure.

A reproductive shoot system (PO:0025082) that develops from an inflorescence (PO:0009049) and has as parts each infructescence axis (PO:0025242) and all of the fruits (PO:0009001) borne by those axes.
A dehiscence zone (PO:0025092) that is part of an anther (PO:0009066).

comments: Extends along the entire length of the anther and is observed as an indentation between the locules of each theca. Upon anther maturation, cell separation within the dehiscence zone allows the anther wall to break open and pollen to be released.

synonyms.val: zona de dehiscencia de la antera (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: A shoot system (PO:0009006) that develops from an embryo shoot apical meristem (PO:0006362).
A septum (PO:0000030) that is part of an anther dehiscence zone (PO:0005011).
A vascular leaf characterized by particular anatomical traits namely, wax and trichome distribution, presence or absence of epidermal cell types, cell wall shape and biochemistry.

comments: Many species have juvenile leaves at the base of the stem, adult leaves at the apex, and transition leaves in between. In maize, juvenile leaves are at the tip of the stalk (stem), which differentiates first, with adult leaves at the base, while other grasses may have other arrangements. In some plants the juvenile leaves may go on to establish as adult leaves.

definition.val: An intercalary meristem (PO:0006073) that is part of a leaf (PO:0006346) and is intercalated between two portions of non-meristematic tissue between a leaf apex (PO:0020137) and a leaf base (PO:0020040).

comments: Results in an increase in length of a leaf, as part of primary growth. If you are annotating to this term, please add an additional annotation to vascular leaf (PO:0009025) or non-vascular leaf (PO:0025075), depending on the species. All annotations for angiosperms, gymnosperms, and pteridophytes should go to vascular leaf and all annotations for bryophytes should go to non-vascular leaf. The leaf intercalary meristem does not include a leaf plate meristem (PO:0025429) .

synonyms.val: 葉 介在 分裂組織 (Japanese, exact)
meristema intercalar de la hoja (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: A portion of endodermis (PO:0000252) that is part of an plant embryo (PO:0009009).
OBSOLETE. A tubular cell extension formed by the germinating pollen grain; carries the male gametes into the ovule.

comments: This term was made obsolete because it is a subcellular component. See GO for the term pollen tube (GO:0090406). Since a pollen tube is part_of a pollen tube cell, annotations for pollen tube may also go to the more general term pollen tube cell (PO:0025195).

definition.val: A portion of cortex (PO:0005708) that is part of a plant embryo (PO:0009009).

comments: Can occur in the hypocotyl and root.

definition.val: A lateral meristem (PO:0020145) that is part of a shoot axis (PO:0025029).
The outermost primary cell layer of the hypocotyl.
A shoot-borne shoot system (PO:0004545) that develops from an axillary bud (PO:0004709).
A shoot axis vascular system (PO:0000039) that includes the totality of the portions of vascular tissue in their specific arrangement in a pedicel (PO:0030112).
The meristem that produces two spikelet meristems, each of which produces two floral meristems.

comments: Found in some grass inflorescences.

synonyms.val: par de meristemas de la espiguilla (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: An inflorescence apical meristem that gives rise to the two or more florets of a grass inflorescence.
A gynoecium in the early stages of development, characterized as a ridge on the abaxial surface of the floral meristem that develops from a gynoecium primordium.

comments: Common in monocots, including species of Poaceae such as Zea mays. If you are annotating to this structure for Zea mays or other grasses, please also add an annotation to the corresponding floret type. Choose the most specific term possible from: spikelet floret (PO:0009082), ear floret (PO:0006354), lower floret of pedicellate spikelet of ear (PO:0006353), lower floret of sessile spikelet of ear (PO:0006351), upper floret of pedicellate spikelet of ear (PO:0006350), upper floret of sessile spikelet of ear (PO:0006352). In Zea mays, development of the gynoecium ridge of the upper floret of pedicellate spikelet of ear occurs via continued overgrowth of the shoot apex (which becomes the ovule primordium) by a ring of gynoecial tissue, leading to the formation of a stylar canal that is detected as a slight protuberance on the mature ovary. Early development of the gynoecium ridge of the lower floret of pedicellate spikelet of ear is very similar to that of the upper floret of the pedicellate spikelet of ear, except the development does not proceed beyond the early ridge stage.

synonyms.val: gynoecium ridge of lower floret of pedicellate spikelet of ear (narrow)
gynoecium ridge of upper floret of pedicellate spikelet of ear (narrow)
gynoecium ridge of upper floret of sessile spikelet of ear (narrow)
gynoecium ridge of lower floret of sessile spikelet of ear (narrow)

definition.val: A shoot axis internode (PO:0005005) that is part of an inflorescence axis (PO:0020122).
A shoot axis node (PO:0005004) that is part of an inflorescence axis (PO:0020122).
A bud that develops into a strobilus.
A bud that develops into a reproductive shoot system.
A reproductive shoot system (PO:0025082) consisting of a number of sporophylls (PO:0009026) or plant ovule (PO:0020003)-bearing modified leaves (PO:0025034) grouped terminally on a stem (PO:0009047).

comments: May be simple or compound. Found in lycophytes such as Selaginella and Lycopodium, sphenophytes such as Equisetum, gymnosperms such as cycad, conifers, gnetophytes and the pollen producing structures of Gingko. The term cone is often used for strobili that are woody. Flowers are sometimes considered bisexual strobili. Some flowering plants such as Alnus have inflorescences called catkins that resemble strobili, but are not.

synonyms.val: 胞子嚢穂,　球花 (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: A shoot system (PO:0009006) in the sporophytic phase that has as part at least one sporangium (PO:0025094).

synonyms.val: 生殖シュート 系、苗条系 (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: An axillary shoot that develops from a subterranean tuber axillary bud.

comments: See also subterranean tuber axillary bud (PO:0025042).

synonyms.val: 地下塊茎腋 分げつ (Japanese, exact)
epiblasto (epiblastema) axilar de tub&#233rculo subterr&#225neo (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: A shoot axis internode (PO:0005005) that is part of a branch (PO:0025073).
A cardinal part of multi-tissue plant structure (PO:0025498) that is a ridge on a seed (PO:0009010) that develops from a raphe (PO:0020027).
A shoot axis that is an elongation of the floral axis that supports the carpels.

comments: A gynophore is only present when there is an elongation of the axis between the androecium and gynoecium.

synonyms.val: 花被間柱、子房柄、雌蕊柄 (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: A cardinal organ part (PO:0025001) of a shoot axis (PO:0025029) where a bud (PO:0000055) may form and develop into a branch (PO:0025073), leaf (PO:0025034), flower (PO:0004541), inflorescence (PO:0009049) or nodal root (PO:0003005).
A trichome that is part of a shoot axis epidermis.

comments: Can occur on a stem or branch.

synonyms.val: シュート軸毛（毛茸、糸状体） (Japanese, exact)
eje de tricoma del epiblasto (epiblastema) (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: A plant anatomical space that is enclosed by and forms an opening in a seed coat at the apex of a seed and is the remnant of a micropyle.
A remnant of the ovular chalaza that is part of the seed.
An axillary branch that forms from a leaf above the very base of the shoot.

comments: The genetic distinction between cauline axillary branches and tillers may or may not be unique to the Poaceae. There are no data for other plant families.

definition.val: An axillary shoot system (PO:0006343) that is part of a stem base (PO:0008039).

comments: Called a tiller in the Poaceae.

definition.val: A cardinal part of multi-tissue plant structure (PO:0025498) that is attached to a seed (PO:0009010) and is the remnants of a funicle (PO:0020006).
A sporophyte meristematic apical cell that is part of a root tip.

comments: Occurs in the sporophytic phase of pteridophytes.

synonyms.val: c&#233lula apical de la ra&#237z (Spanish, exact)
根分裂組織の頂端細胞 (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: An axillary shoot that develops from an aerial tuber axillary bud.

synonyms.val: epiblasto (epiblastema) axilar de tub&#233rculo a&#233reo (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: A single meristematic cell (PO:0004010) at the tip of a plant structure where apical growth occurs.

comments: Apical cells occur only at the tip of a shoot axis apex, leaf apex, root apex, thallus apex, or protonema in bryophytes and some pteridophytes. Apical growth results from division of a single meristematic cell located at the tip of an apical meristem or plant organ, rather than from a population of meristematic cells located at the tip of an apical meristem. The apical cell may be tetrahedral shaped, with three (in shoots) or four (in roots) cutting faces, or wedge-shaped (lenticular) with two cutting faces (in non-vascular leaves or thalli). An apical cell may be established upon germination of a spore or upon the first cell division of an embryo, or later.

synonyms.val: 分裂組織の頂端細胞 (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: A tassel floret that is one of the two florets placed above the lower floret on a sessile spikelet rachilla of a tassel inflorescence.

synonyms.val: 雄穂（花）の無柄小穂の上位小花 (Japanese, exact)
florete superior de la espiguilla s&#233sil (Spanish, exact)

nodes.lbl: upper floret of sessile spikelet of tassel

definition.val: A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) at the interface between two plant structures, one of which is in a gametophyte development stage (PO:0028003) and one of which is in a sporophyte development stage (PO:0028002), and that has as parts transfer cells (PO:0000078).

comments: The transfer cells aid in nutrient transport. Examples include ovary placenta (PO:0020001) and fruit placenta (PO:0004535).

definition.val: A terminal reproductive bud that develops into a strobilus.

A gametophyte development stage during which a gametophyte undergoes filamentous growth and that succeeds spore germination and precedes a thalloid development stage (planar growth) or gametophore development stage.

comments: The protonema phase ends with the development of gametophores in mosses, some other bryophytes, and leptosporangiate ferns and with the development of a thallus in other bryophytes, although protonema tissue may persist of continue to develop after this.

synonyms.val: 原糸体を形成する植物発生段階 (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: A tassel floret that is the lower of the two florets of a sessile spikelet of a tassel inflorescence.

synonyms.val: florete inferior de la espiguilla s&#233sil (Spanish, exact)
雄穂（花）の無柄小穂の下位小花 (Japanese, exact)

nodes.lbl: lower floret of sessile spikelet of tassel

definition.val: A portion of protonema tissue that consists of only caulonema cells.

comments: Generally, the development of caulonema follows the development of chloronema. Only the caulonema, and not the chloronema, initiates gametophore buds.

definition.val: A tassel floret that is one of the two florets placed above the lower floret on a pedicellate spikelet rachilla of a tassel inflorescence.

synonyms.val: florete superior de la espiguilla pedicelada (Spanish, exact)
雄穂（花）の有柄小穂の上位小花 (Japanese, exact)

nodes.lbl: upper floret of pedicellate spikelet of tassel

definition.val: An axillary reproductive bud that develops into a strobilus.

synonyms.val: 腋珠果（ストロビル）芽 (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: A leaf (PO:0025034) in a non-vascular plant.

comments: Non-vascular leaves occur in the gametophyte development stage (PO:0028003) of Bryophytes, plants such as moss and liverwort.

definition.val: A megagametophyte (PO:0025279) that is located in a plant ovary ovule (PO:0025490).

comments: Produces an embryo sac egg cell (PO:0025123).

definition.val: Inflorescence branch that terminates in a spikelet.

comments: This is not a pedicel in the strict sense, but is the ultimate naked part of the inflorescence axis.

definition.val: A shoot axis (PO:00025029) that develops from an axillary bud meristem (PO:0000232) or from equal divisions of a meristematic apical cell (PO:0030007).

comments: In vascular plants, branches arise from an axillary bud meristem (PO:0000232) and from divisions of the meristematic apical cell (PO:0030007) in non-vascular plants.

definition.val: A meristematic apical cell that is part of a shoot system.

comments: May occur in shoot axes or leaves of bryophytes or ferns.

definition.val: An axillary bud (PO:0004709) that develops into an reproductive shoot system (PO:0025082).

definition.val: A portion of protonema tissue that consists of only chloronema cells.

comments: Generally, the development of chloronema precedes the development of caulonema. Only the caulonema, and not the chloronema, initiates gametophore buds.

definition.val: A portion of chlorenchyma tissue that develops directly from a spore and grows by division of an apical cell to form filaments that are one cell wide and dichotomously branching.

comments: The protonema is the first structure that develops in the gametophytic phase of mosses, some other bryophytes, and leptosporangiate ferns. The term protonema is also used to refer to the phase of development in which protonemal tissue is produced (see PO:0030006 protonema phase). In some species of moss, the protonema is perennial. A protonema may develop from sporophytic tissue during apospory.

definition.val: A chlorenchyma cell that is part of a caulonema and has cross walls of adjacent cells that are oblique to the protonema axis.

comments: A caulonema cell contains fewer, less well-developed chloroplasts than a chloronema cell.

definition.val: A chlorenchyma cell that is part of a chloronema and has cross walls of adjacent cells that are perpendicular to the protonema axis.

comments: A chloronema cell contains many well-developed chloroplasts.

definition.val: A spikelet (PO:0009051) that is part of the ear inflorescence (PO:0020136) and bears a single ear floret (PO:0006354) at maturity.

comments: The ear spikelet forms with two ear florets (PO:0006354), but the lower one aborts during development.

definition.val: A first order inflorescence axis (PO:0025104) that is the primary axis of a tassel inflorescence (PO:0020126).

synonyms.val: espiga central del penacho (borla) de la inflorescencia (Spanish, exact)

definition.val: An inflorescence branch (PO:0009081) arising on a first order tassel inflorescence axis (PO:0006324) or from a higher order inflorescence branch (PO:0009081) that is part of a tassel inflorescence (PO:0020126).
A higher order inflorescence axis (PO:0009081) that develops from an inflorescence axillary meristem (PO:0009105) of a second order inflorescence axis (PO:0006322).

definition.val: A shoot lateral meristem (PO:0006344) that is part of a shoot axis (PO:0025029) and has a parts multiple layers of meristematic cells (PO:0004010) located near the shoot apical meristem (PO:0020148).

comments: Contributes to primary thickening of a shoot axis (PO:0025029), adventitious (shoot-borne) root (PO:0000042) formation, and formation of linkages between shot axis (PO:0000039), leaf (PO:0000036), and root (PO:0003011) vascular systems. Contiguous with the shoot apical meristem (PO:0020148) in some species, but not all. Produces more or less distinct vascular bundles (PO:0005020) surrounded by ground tissue (PO:0025059), as opposed to the more or less continuous xylem (PO:0005352) and phloem (PO:0005417) produced by a vascular cambium (PO:0005598). A primary thickening meristem is a multi-layered structure, compared to the single layer of a cambium. Found in many monocotyledons.

synonyms.val: 一次 肥厚（膜）分裂組織 (Japanese, exact)

definition.val: A lower glume that is part of an ear spikelet.

definition.val: A peripheral portion of ground tissue (PO:0025059) in a plant axis (PO:0025004) that is composed of cork cambium (phellogen; PO:0005599), phellem (PO:0004003), and phelloderm (PO:0005050).

comments: After secondary growth, the periderm may replace the epidermis in stems and roots, rarely in other organs. In some cases, the epidermis is retained after periderm development. Periderm is derived from lateral meristem and may contain secondary phloem.

definition.val: An inflorescence apical meristem that gives rise to the maize tassel.
A primordium (PO:0025127) that develops from a root anlagen (PO:0025433) and is committed to the development of a root (PO:0009005).

comments: A root primordium may arise from cells of a pericycle (PO:0006203) in a root in most seed plant (pericyclic lateral root primordium; PO:0025492), from cells of an endodermis (PO:0000252) in ferns and some seed plants (non-pericyclic lateral root primordium: PO:0025493), or from cells of a shoot axis (PO:0025029), in the case of a basal root primordium (PO:0025479) or shoot-borne root primordium (PO:0025480). Transition from root primordium to root occurs with the formation of a root cap (PO:0020123), shortly after the development of a root apical meristem (PO:0020147).

definition.val: A shoot system vascular system  (PO:0025205) that includes the totality of the portions of vascular tissue in their specific arrangement in an inflorescence (PO:0009049).

Multinucleate cell developed by a series of events involving fusion with the neighboring dividing cells. The events are induced by cyst nematodes (e.g. Heterodera schachtii) entering the feeding cells (any cells) of the root vascular system.
The meristem present on short tassel branch that produces two spikelet meristems, each of which produces two floral meristems in a maize tassel.

synonyms.val: par de meristemas del penacho (borla) de la espiguilla (Spanish, exact)

comments: One of the major chalconoids from hops is xanthohumol (CHEBI:66331).
